Package com.cafean.client.analysis

Class ComponentNumberGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.analysis.ComponentNumberGroup
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    OrderedComponentNumberGroup
    public class ComponentNumberGroup
extends java.lang.Object
    The ComponentNumberGroup is a controller for determining pools of unique component numbers for abstract components. Each group has a name for error messages, an initial value, a maximum value, and the increment. This group gets associated with an array of categories that are searched through.

        public ComponentNumberGroup​(java.lang.String name,
                            int initial,
                            int maximum,
                            int increment,
                            Category[] categories)
        Creates a new instance of ComponentNumberGroup. Each group represents a grouping of components that share a pool of component numbers.
        Parameters:
        name - a String containing the name of this group
        initial - the first number in this group
        maximum - the last number in this group
        increment - the quantity added to the current component number to determine the proper next
        categories - a Category[] containing the Categories that are part of this group.

        public int getInitial()
        Retrieves the first CC number available to components of the given component class. This is simply the initial value of the pool of possible CC numbers for the given cc group.

        NOTE: The returned CC number may or may not be in use.

        Returns:
        the starting CC number for this group.

      • next

        public int next​(AbstractModel model,
                int requestedNumber)
        Retrieves a new and available CC number for this component group. If the requested cc number of available it will be returned, otherwise the next available CC number will be returned.

        Available is defined as: greater than or equal to the initial cc number, lower than or equal to the maximum cc number and not currently used by another component in the given cc group.

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel that is being searched.
        requestedNumber - The desired CC number. If it is available, it will be returned.
        Returns:
        the requested cc number if available or a newly allocate cc number.

      • next

        public int next​(AbstractModel model,
                AbstractComponent component,
                int requestedNumber)
        Retrieves a new and available component number for this component group. If the requested component number of available it will be returned, otherwise the next available component number will be returned.

        Available is defined as: greater than or equal to the initial component number, lower than or equal to the maximum component number and not currently used by another component in the given group.

        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel that is being searched.
        component - the AbstractComponent that will receive the new number
        requestedNumber - The desired component number. If it is available, it will be returned.
        Returns:
        the requested number if available or a newly allocated number.

      • check

        public boolean check​(AbstractModel model,
                     java.lang.String emptyMsg,
                     java.lang.String listName,
                     java.lang.String context,
                     boolean warnEmpty,
                     boolean adjust)
        Checks that all CC numbers in for this group in the given model are valid and unique. Errors are printed for invalid and duplicate cc numbers.
        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel that is being searched.
        emptyMsg - a String containing the empty list message such as There are no
        listName - the name of the given list of components
        context - a String containing a description of the given context such as in this model.
        warnEmpty - if true a warning will be added to the MessageWindow if components is empty.
        adjust - if true when a component number is out of range, it will be adjusted to an available number inside the range.
